    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras are positioned for a high-ceiling offensive output today, anchored by **Pete Crow-Armstrong**, who earns our highest efficiency score of 80.98. Facing Petty\u2019s unfavorable 6.57 xERA, **Pete Crow-Armstrong** benefits from a massive 19% SP skill boost and favorable wind conditions, making him our primary target for stolen base production. **Trea Turner** (66.43) and **Carson Benge** (67.23) round out our top-tier plays; **Trea Turner** capitalizes on his premier leadoff spot against Junk, while **Carson Benge** finds himself in an ideal platoon situation with a park factor surge that overrides his lower batting position. Despite facing a formidable arm in Yamamoto, **Yordan Alvarez** remains a core start (60.60) due to his elite 0.427 xwOBA, which consistently mitigates even the toughest pitching matchups.\n\nIn terms of bench decisions, **Luke Raley** (56.56) stands as the most difficult omission, narrowly missing the cut behind our higher-projected starters. While **Luke Raley** enjoys a significant 14% skill edge against Ritchie, his lower base projection in a park that penalizes his profile kept him from displacing **Dillon Dingler** (56.77). **Dillon Dingler** earns the nod at C1 primarily due to the rare dynamic platoon advantage against Tolle, which outweighed the risk of a sub-4.00 xERA opponent. We are closely monitoring the status of **Christian Yelich**, who remains on the IL, alongside minor-league prospects **Zac Veen**, **Luis Pena**, and **Pedro Ramirez**, who provide depth but remain unavailable for today's roster. We are also sitting on **Caleb Durbin**, **Gary Sanchez**, **Lars Nootbaar**, and **Josh Smith**, who serve as our primary depth pieces should any late-scratches occur in the starting lineup.",
